Package edu.depauw.csc232.solitaire.ui

Class Pile

java.lang.Object
edu.depauw.csc232.solitaire.ui.CardStack
edu.depauw.csc232.solitaire.ui.Pile
public class Pile
extends CardStack
A Pile is a CardStack located on a game Table. It has a PileStrategy to be able to respond to mouse clicks and drag/drop events.
Author:
bhoward

    • canDrag

      public boolean canDrag​(java.awt.event.MouseEvent event)
      Return whether the given pile may be dragged. This could be used to change the mouse appearance, for example. To avoid lag, this should do minimal computation and return quickly.
      Parameters:
      event - the mouseDragged event being checked
      Returns:
      true if this pile will respond to being dragged

      Returns:
